<p style="Normal" xid="4"><c>﻿Virtual Identity Defender p34</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="7"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="8" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr"><c>https://www.cognizant.com/whitepapers/21-more-jobs-of-the-future-a-guide-to-getting-and-staying-employed-through-2029-codex3928.pdf</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="5"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="9"><c>You never get a second chance to make a first impression.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="10"><c>Purpose of a CV : get an interview</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="11"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="12"><c>It must : </c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="14"><c>Attract</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="15"><c>Inform related to the job description</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="16"><c>Persuade with skills, past experiences,</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="17"><c>Sell</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="18"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="19"><c>It musn’t :</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="20"><c>A resume/CV is not a book</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="21"><c>A resume/CV is not an obstacle</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="22"><c>A resume/CV is not a tombstone</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="23"><c>A resume/CV is not boring or difficult to read</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="25"><c>A resume/CV is not you lifestory</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="26"><c>A resume/CV is not a catalogue of your personal opinions</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="27"><c>A resume/CV is not a list of problems with past employers</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="29"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="30"><c>A CV is short, sedeuctive, an important document, answers the question Why, interesting and easy to read, list of benefits for the employer, as much about the employer as about you.</c></p>
